# lsof

#### ENG

`lsof` command is a bit different than other commands. The main purpose of `lsof` is get information about which pid opens the file by tracking `/proc` file to get information about opened files.
You may or may not see all pid's, opened files and their file descriptor according to your user privileges. Use `lsof` root if you want to see all the table. what i made is a very minimal implementation. Original command offers a lot of options.
